==Populated places established by VOC people==
[[File:Moederkerk Swellendam.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Cape Dutch architecture|Cape Dutch style]]-influenced eclectic building of the [[Nederduitse Gereformeerde Kerk]] in [[Swellendam]]. The [[Cape Dutch architecture]], along with [[Afrikaans language]] and [[Afrikaans literature]], is among the lasting legacy of the VOC-era [[Afrikaners|Afrikaans culture]] in South Africa.]]
Populated places (including cities, towns and villages) established/founded{{efn|i.e., first settled or otherwise came into existence.}} by people of the Dutch East India Company (VOC).
* [[Batavia, Dutch East Indies|Batavia]] ([[Dutch East Indies]]), modern-day [[History of Jakarta|Jakarta]]
* [[Tainan]], the oldest urban area in Taiwan, located in southern-western Taiwan
* [[Kaohsiung]] (formerly known as Takao or [[Dagao]]), located in southern-western Taiwan
* [[Kaapstad]] ([[Cape Town]]), the oldest urban area in South Africa and one of the first permanent European settlements in [[Sub-Saharan Africa]]. [[Constantia, Cape Town|Constantia]] ([[List of Cape Town suburbs|Cape Town's suburb]]) is considered one of the oldest [[wine-producing region]]s in the [[Southern Hemisphere]].
* [[Stellenbosch]], the second oldest urban area (town) in South Africa
* [[Swellendam]], the third oldest urban area (town) in South Africa
* [[Graaff-Reinet]], the fourth oldest urban area (town) in South Africa
* [[Franschhoek]], a town in the [[Western Cape Province]], South Africa
* [[Paarl]], the third oldest European settlement in South Africa and the largest town in the [[Cape Winelands]]
* [[Simonstad]] ([[Simon's Town]]), a town near Cape Town, South Africa
* [[Dutch Mauritius]], the first permanent [[human settlement]] ever in [[History of Mauritius|Mauritius]]{{efn| named after [[Maurice of Nassau]], [[Prince of Orange]], the [[Stadtholder]] of all the provinces of the Dutch Republic (except for Friesland) from 1585 until his death in 1625.}}

==Important heritage sites in the VOC World==
{{See also|:Category:Former settlements and colonies of the Dutch East India Company|l1=Former settlements and colonies of the Dutch East India Company (VOC)|:Category:Former trading posts of the Dutch East India Company|l2=Former trading posts of the Dutch East India Company (VOC)|:Category:Former properties of the Dutch East India Company|l3=Former properties of the Dutch East India Company (VOC)|:Category:Populated places established by the Dutch East India Company|l4=Populated places established by the Dutch East India Company (VOC)|:Category:Buildings and structures associated with the Dutch East India Company|l5=Buildings and structures associated with the Dutch East India Company (VOC)}}

* Netherlands: Amsterdam (the VOC's global headquarters); [[Zaandam]] (one of the world's earliest known industrialized areas and the VOC's shipbuilding centre)
* Indonesia: [[History of Jakarta|Jakarta]], the VOC's second headquarters and ''de facto'' administrative center
* Sri Lanka: [[Galle]], a [[UNESCO World Heritage Site]]
* South Africa: [[Western Cape]] ([[Cape Town]]; [[Stellenbosch]]; [[Swellendam]]; [[Franschhoek]]; [[Paarl]]), the first urban areas to be established in South Africa
* Taiwan: [[Tainan]], the first urban area to be established in Taiwan
* Japan: [[Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki]] ([[Hirado, Nagasaki|Hirado]] & [[Dejima]])
* Malaysia: [[Malacca City|Malacca]], a UNESCO World Heritage Site
* Australia: [[Western Australia]] ([[Dirk Hartog Island]] & [[Houtman Abrolhos]]){{efn|See articles: [[History of Western Australia]]; [[Shipwrecks of Western Australia]]; [[Brouwer Route]]; [[Hartog Plate]].}}

